Basbousa
  --Vian Alnidawi and Sara Nassr

Cake:
2 c fine semolina
2 c dried, unsweetened coconut
2 c sugar
2 c ap flour
1 tsp kosher salt
1 c plain whole milk yogurt
3 eggs
2 tsp baking powder
2 tsp vanilla

Preheat oven to 350F. In a bowl, combine all ingredients into a thick batter and press into either a 9x13" baking dish or a 10" springform that's been greased and lined with parchment. Bake for 20-25 min until the center is set. Turn the oven to broil for 3-4 min to brown the top. Let cool.

Syrup:
1 1/4 c sugar
1 1/4 c water
1 tsp lemon juice

In a saucepan, combine sugar and water over high heat; boil until sugar is completely dissolved. Add the lemon juice and allow the syrup to cool slightly before slowly pouring over the cake until it's completely absorbed.

Serving:
finely chopped pistachios
unsweetened coconut

To serve, cut into pieces and garnish with pistachios and coconut.
